This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to improve the accuracy of word embeddings. Specifically, it focuses on definition modeling, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses Gumble-Softmax, a probabilistic approach commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG), and discusses the use of word sense decompositions, which is a technique used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to disambiguate word senses. The paper also evaluates the performance of the model in terms of recall and precision, which are metrics commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
